                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>The paper praises the Bathing Rooms fitted up by F. Schaffer, proprietor of
                    the Virginia Hotel.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper writes a review of the Ames N. O. Circus and Menagerie. The
                    article praises a number of acts including the trapezists, somersault and
                    juggling acts on horseback, a contortionist, the animal acts, and the minstrel
                    concert that included a "life-like delineation of negro character."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Dry</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper reports that the weather has been very dry recently, and that the
                    corn crop is a failure.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper gives an account of Old John Robinson's Circus that performed in
                    Staunton "to the largest crowd we ever saw under one canvas." The article
                    praises the leaping, tight-rope walking, and various tricks on horseback.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
